32-118.01.Special election, defined.

Special election shall mean an election other than a regularly scheduled primary or general election as specified in statute or by home rule charter.

SourceLaws 1997, LB 764, ยง 12.

Annotations

Special election is defined by this section. Arends v. Whitten, 172 Neb. 297, 109 N.W.2d 363 (1961).
